A **pear diamond pendant** is the single most impactful piece of fine jewelry you can wear at the collarbone. The teardrop silhouette, positioned at the décolletage and viewed face-on, reads at its full face-up size — something a ring finger never gives you. This guide covers every pear diamond pendant at Blue Nile and James Allen: point-up bezel solitaires, point-up prong solitaires, east-west bezel solitaires, collar pendants, and the full natural vs lab-grown decision framework, from 1/4 CTW to 3 CTW.

Whether you are shopping for a **pear diamond solitaire pendant** as a daily-wear piece, a **1 carat pear shaped diamond pendant** as a milestone gift, a **pear shaped diamond pendant necklace** in yellow gold or platinum, or comparing a **bezel set pear diamond necklace** against a Tiffany alternative, every current option with live {{month}} {{year}} prices is catalogued below with affiliate links. If you need the full necklace guide including tennis necklaces, see our [pear diamond necklace guide](/pear-diamond-necklace).

**TL;DR:** Decide setting type before you look at a single price. → If you wear jewelry every day, buy the bezel — the metal rim protects the pointed pear tip and the piece will outlast every trend. If you wear it occasionally, buy the prong for maximum sparkle. Once that is settled: lab diamonds give you three times the stone for the same money as natural. The [1 ct lab point-up pendant in 14K Yellow Gold at $930](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/point-up-pear-cut-lab-grown-diamond-solitaire-pendant-in-14k-yellow-gold-1-ct-tw-f-g-vs2-si1-item-251324?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) is the single most over-delivered value in this entire guide. For daily-wear natural, start with the [JA Bezel 0.25 ct in Yellow Gold at $892](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/bezel-solitaire-pendant-necklace-with-025-ctw-pear-shaped-diamond-in-14k-yellow-gold-by-james-allen-item-310934?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational). Everything else — carat size, chain length, metal color — is secondary to those two decisions.

> **Contrarian Truth:** Nobody needs a 3 ct pendant to make a statement. The collarbone is the closest viewing position in all of jewelry — a 1 ct pear worn at 16" reads larger there than a 2 ct worn on a ring. The [1 ct lab in 14K Yellow Gold at $930](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/point-up-pear-cut-lab-grown-diamond-solitaire-pendant-in-14k-yellow-gold-1-ct-tw-f-g-vs2-si1-item-251324?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) is the most over-delivered value in this entire guide.

