## The Tiffany Question

The semantic keyword "pear-shaped diamond necklace Tiffany" captures buyers comparing Tiffany to alternatives. Tiffany sells pear diamond pendants and does so beautifully — but at premiums that reflect brand value, not stone value. A comparable Tiffany bezel pear pendant in platinum at 0.25 ct retails at $3,500–$5,000 depending on grading. The [JA Bezel 0.25 ct Natural in Platinum at $1,001](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/bezel-solitaire-pendant-necklace-with-025-ctw-pear-shaped-diamond-in-platinum-by-james-allen-item-310935?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) is the Blue Nile equivalent: natural diamond, platinum, bezel-set, GIA-certifiable stone. The difference is brand markup, not product quality.

If you need the Tiffany box for a gift, buy Tiffany. If you need the Tiffany quality in platinum with a natural diamond, the [JA Bezel Platinum series](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/bezel-solitaire-pendant-necklace-with-075-ctw-pear-shaped-diamond-in-platinum-by-james-allen-item-310941?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) at Blue Nile delivers it at 60–70% of the Tiffany retail price.

