## Frequently Asked Questions

**What is the best carat for a pear diamond pendant?**
1 ct is the visual sweet spot for most wearers — visible at social distances without feeling heavy. In lab-grown, the [1 ct F-G/VS2-SI1 in yellow gold at $930](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/point-up-pear-cut-lab-grown-diamond-solitaire-pendant-in-14k-yellow-gold-1-ct-tw-f-g-vs2-si1-item-251324?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) is the benchmark. For natural, the practical entry is 0.25–0.5 ct because natural pear pricing rises sharply above that.

**What is the difference between a bezel and prong-set pear pendant?**
A bezel fully encircles the stone including the tip — maximum protection, modern look, ideal for daily wear. A prong setting uses minimal metal contact for maximum stone visibility — more sparkle, traditional look, but the pear tip is exposed. The Tip Vulnerability Rule: buy the bezel for every-day wear.

**What metal is best for a pear diamond solitaire pendant?**
For lab-grown pendants, 14K yellow gold is ideal — durable, warm, no maintenance, and complements F-G color stones. For natural diamond pendants, platinum is worth the premium: it holds bezels and prongs indefinitely, never needs replating, and the [JA Bezel Platinum series](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/bezel-solitaire-pendant-necklace-with-025-ctw-pear-shaped-diamond-in-platinum-by-james-allen-item-310935?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) is designed to last a lifetime.

**Is a 1 carat pear shaped diamond pendant worth it?**
Yes, especially in lab-grown. The [1 ct lab in 14K Yellow Gold at $930](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/point-up-pear-cut-lab-grown-diamond-solitaire-pendant-in-14k-yellow-gold-1-ct-tw-f-g-vs2-si1-item-251324?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) at F-G/VS2-SI1 is extraordinarily good value. A natural 1 ct pear pendant at equivalent grade costs $8,000–$10,000. The face-up appearance at the collarbone is identical.

**What chain length should I choose for a pear diamond pendant?**
16" places the pendant at the collarbone — formal, elegant, maximum visibility. 18" is the most versatile all-occasion length. 20" reads casual. The Chain Length Illusion means the same stone reads differently at each length. Buy 16–18" for the best impact from your pendant's stone size.

**Is lab-grown or natural better for a pear diamond pendant?**
Lab for size per dollar: [3 ct lab at $2,292](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/point-up-pear-cut-lab-grown-diamond-solitaire-pendant-in-14k-yellow-gold-3-ct-tw-f-g-vs2-si1-item-251327?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) vs natural 1 ct at $6,820+. Natural for investment value and provenance: [JA Bezel 1 ct Platinum at $5,859](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/bezel-solitaire-pendant-necklace-with-1-ctw-pear-shaped-diamond-in-platinum-by-james-allen-item-310944?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) is an asset. Lab stones do not hold resale value; natural stones do.

**What is the difference between point-up and east-west for a pear pendant?**
Point-up creates a vertical teardrop silhouette that elongates the neckline — romantic, classic, feminine. East-west rotates the stone 90° to a horizontal silhouette — modern, architectural, fashion-forward. The [EW Bezel 0.25 CTW at $1,220](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/east-west-bezel-solitaire-pendant-necklace-with-025-ctw-pear-shaped-diamond-in-14k-white-gold-item-297496?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) and the [Point Up 1/4 ct at $600](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/point-up-pear-cut-lab-grown-diamond-solitaire-pendant-in-14k-yellow-gold-1-4-ct-tw-f-g-vs2-si1-item-251318?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) are fundamentally different aesthetic choices.

**What clarity grade do I need for a pear diamond pendant?**
SI1–VS2 is the practical range. Pendants are viewed at 18+ inches from the observer — SI1 is completely eye-clean at that distance under any lighting. The [lab-grown F-G/VS2-SI1 range](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/point-up-pear-cut-lab-grown-diamond-solitaire-pendant-in-14k-yellow-gold-1-ct-tw-f-g-vs2-si1-item-251324?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) is the optimal sweet spot — any cleaner is invisible value at pendant viewing distances.

**Can I wear a pear diamond pendant every day?**
Yes, with the right setting. A bezel-set pendant — like the [JA Bezel series](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/bezel-solitaire-pendant-necklace-with-025-ctw-pear-shaped-diamond-in-14k-yellow-gold-by-james-allen-item-310934?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) or the [EW Bezel series](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/east-west-bezel-solitaire-pendant-necklace-with-025-ctw-pear-shaped-diamond-in-14k-white-gold-item-297496?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) — is designed for daily wear. The Tip Vulnerability Rule applies: prong-set pear pendants are better for occasional wear where the tip exposure risk is managed.

**What is a pear diamond solitaire pendant?**
A single pear-shaped diamond set alone in a pendant, with no accent stones. All options in this guide are solitaires. The term distinguishes single-stone pendants from halo pendants (center stone surrounded by smaller accent diamonds) or multi-stone drops. Solitaires are the most versatile — they work across casual, business, and formal contexts.

**Is the Tiffany pear diamond necklace worth the premium?**
Tiffany offers excellent quality and brand prestige. The premium is roughly 3–5x equivalent stones at Blue Nile for an equivalent bezel-set natural pendant. If the blue box matters — for a gift, for branding — Tiffany is worth it. If the jewelry itself is the priority, the [JA Bezel 0.25 ct Natural Platinum at $1,001](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/bezel-solitaire-pendant-necklace-with-025-ctw-pear-shaped-diamond-in-platinum-by-james-allen-item-310935?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) is the quality-equivalent alternative at a fraction of the price.

**How do I choose between a pear diamond pendant and a pear diamond ring?**
A pendant is visible at maximum face-up size — the collarbone presents it straight-on at close range. A ring stone is viewed from above at an angle and competes with the setting and hand. Dollar for dollar, a pendant shows more stone. If budget is limited, a [1 ct pear lab pendant at $930](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/point-up-pear-cut-lab-grown-diamond-solitaire-pendant-in-14k-yellow-gold-1-ct-tw-f-g-vs2-si1-item-251324?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) makes more visual impact than the same stone in a ring. For engagement symbolism, see our [pear diamond engagement ring guide](/pear-diamond-engagement-ring).

